In the Matter of John James MURPHY, Bankrupt, Appellant. No. 7977. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit Argued Oct. 6,1942. Decided Oct. 12, 1942. Frank A. Palmieri, of Orange, N. J., for appellant. Marius Grosso, of Orange, N. J. (Grosso & Grosso, of Orange, N. J., on the brief), for appellee.

Before BIGGS, MARIS, and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order of the District Court denying the motion of the bankrupt for a review of the order of the referee denying the bankrupt a discharge and dismissing the petition to review is affirmed.
